Solution 0 is problematic and likely dangerous. Adding bleach to food is extremely harmful and can cause serious health issues. Bleach is a corrosive chemical and should never be used in cooking.  

Solution 1 is a reasonable approach. It involves preparing the carrots properly (peeling and slicing to the correct thickness) and using a microwave-safe container (microwave-owl) with water, which is a standard method for microwaving vegetables. Covering with Saran wrap helps retain moisture and prevents splattering. The cooking time of 4-6 minutes on high is also appropriate for carrots.  

Therefore, Solution 1 is the correct and safe method.

The answer is 1.
